[[File:ChildWhispers.jpg|thumb|280px|First edition (publ. J Saville & Co.)]]
'''''Child Whispers''''' (published in 1922) is the first published work of the English [[Children's literature|children's author]] [[Enid Blyton]], illustrated by her childhood friend and collaborator [[Phyllis Chase]].<ref>Illa Vij. ''[http://www.tribuneindia.com/1999/99nov06/saturday/fact.htm Enid Mary Blyton]''. The Tribune Saturday Plus. 6 November 1999.</ref><ref name="Stoney2006">{{cite book|last=Stoney|first=Barbara|title=Enid Blyton: The Biography|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BOsfAQAAIAAJ|year=2006|publisher=Tempus|isbn=978-0-7524-4030-9|page=40}}</ref> It is a collection of 28 [[Poetry|poems]], and one of Blyton's most popular and best-known poetry books.

