{{italic title}}
{{Unreferenced|date=July 2016}}
'''''Elegy for Iris''''' is a 1999 memoir by [[John Bayley (writer)|John Bayley]], about his marriage to fellow author [[Iris Murdoch]], who suffered from [[Alzheimer's disease]] in her last years. Bayley also wrote two more books about his life with Murdoch, ''Iris and Her Friends'' and ''[[Widower's House]]''.

In 2001, the film ''[[Iris (2001 film)|Iris]]'' was based on Bayley's book. Part of the movie and the book on the life of Iris Murdoch both dealt with her view of marriage, in which she felt it was acceptable for her to engage in adultery. Her husband, John Bayley, knew about her acts of infidelity, especially with one lover in particular. He tolerated it throughout their marriage.

==First edition==
*St. Martin's Press, 1999, {{ISBN|0-312-19864-7}} (hardbound)

